# 🎤 Interview Questions

## 1. What is HTML5 Drag & Drop API?

It allows users to drag HTML elements and drop them into another valid container.

---

## 2. Why use draggable="true"?

It enables dragging for an HTML element.

---

## 3. What is dragstart?

It runs when dragging begins.

---

## 4. What is dragover?

It allows an element to accept dropped items.

Usually:

```javascript
event.preventDefault();
```

---

## 5. What is drop?

Runs when the dragged element is released inside another container.

---

## 6. What is dragend?

Runs after dragging finishes.

---

## 7. What is dataset?

It accesses custom HTML data attributes.

Example

```javascript
element.dataset.id
```

---

## 8. Why use localStorage?

To save tasks after page refresh.

---

## 9. Why use filter()?

To remove tasks.

---

## 10. Why use find()?

To locate a specific task for editing or moving.

---

## 11. Explain Drag & Drop flow.

```
dragstart

↓

Store ID

↓

dragover

↓

drop

↓

Update Status

↓

Save

↓

Render Again
```

---

## 12. What is the difference between dragstart and drop?

dragstart begins dragging.

drop completes the move.

---

## 13. Why call renderTasks() after drop?

To refresh the UI so the task appears in the correct column.

---

## 14. Why use status?

Status determines which column displays the task.

---

## 15. How does Trello work?

Every card has a status.

Dragging changes only the status.

The UI re-renders based on the updated status.

